<subSubSection id="C31887FB5944727CE592FF58FF63FE34" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BBDD4705944727CE592FF58FEAEFF44" blockId="7.[151,266,223,249]" box="[151,266,223,249]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<heading id="D0F5631C5944727CE592FF58FEAEFF44" box="[151,266,223,249]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="B97608625944727CE592FF58FEAEFF44" bold="true" box="[151,266,223,249]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBDD4705944727CE592FEA0FF63FE34" blockId="7.[151,1437,295,465]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Distinguished by small size of adults, macropterous males, apterous females. In addition, the stridulatory file of males is positioned on a raised swelling (e.g. 
<figureCitation id="1339C8F55944727CE793FECCFC85FEDB" box="[662,801,331,358]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="62.[151,198,1832,1856]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-21@62.[151,1435,181,1808]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="FIG. 20. Stridulatory files. A. Australiagraecia spina holotype. B. Australiagraecia minuta. C. Ganiagraecia karwnia, Cytol. prep. 85-19. D. Ganiagraecia karwinia, S-363. E. Gwynnagraecia viridis, Kerragullen. F. Gwynnagraecia perplexa, Fitzgerald River. G. Latitatagraecia kalamaya, Cytol. prep. 2001-1. H. Latitatagraecia vulgivaga, Cytol. prep. 88-66. I. Cooloolagraecia wallum, paratopotype. J. Cooloolagraecia gubbi, paratopotype. K. Kokominiagraecia dicra, S-373. L. Coptaspis sp. 2. M. Timabarragraecia samneilli, paratopotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5602550" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5602550/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Figs 20A, B</figureCitation>
). The stridulatory file is short and the number of teeth is low.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
